anthropy. He is the co-founder and board president of Random Acts, a non-profit organization, as well as the founder of GISH, The Greatest International Scavenger Hunt, known for their charity donations and Guinness World Records. His most recent projects include a poetry book titled \'Some Things I Still Can\'t Tell You\', being the host and executive producer of the PBS show \'Roadfood: Discovering America One Dish at a Time\',  and the fiction podcast \'Bridgewater\', where he is an executive producer and stars as Jeremy Bradshaw. He has been cast as Harvey Dent/Two-Face in the CW\'s upcoming DC show, Gotham Knights.','1974-08-20','None',2,'http://linktr.ee/mishacollins','nm0172557',42747,'Acting','Misha Collins','Boston, Massachusetts, USA','13.698','/kplIxo3cQrEMEYz8YqZOgKDQjgB.jpg',NULL),(4701,0,'[\'Keith Sarabaiyka\', \'Keith Sarabajka\', \'Keith Sarabatchka\', \'Keith Szarabaijka\', \'Keith Szarabajak\', \'Keith Szarabajika\', \'Kieth Szarabajka\', \'Keith Szarabajkap\', \'Keith Szarabjaka\', \'Keith Szarabjka\', \'Keith Szarajka\', \'Keith Szrabajka\']','Keith Szarabajka is an actor and writer.','1952-12-02','None',2,NULL,'nm0843775',87957,'Acting','Keith Szarabajka','Oak Park, Illinois, USA','5.332','/drXhJoVUmm352h4G1QWnvHZgudT.jpg',NULL),(4702,0,'[]','From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia.\n\nShane McRae (born 23 July 1977) is an American actor. He appeared in Hack, guest starred on One Life to Live, Law and Order: Criminal Intent, and Cold Case, and was one of the stars of the ill-fated sitcom, Four Kings.\n\nMcRae was born in Gainesville, Florida.[1] In theatre, McRae played the part of Jason Chenier in the Tony-winning play Take Me Out. In 2005 McRae appeared in Richard III as Richard\'s nemesis, Richmond. He currently resides in New York. He completed a MFA from NYU in 2003. He appears with his \"The Collective\" co-star, Kelly Overton, in the music video for the song \"Terrified\" by Katherine McPhee with Zachary Levi.','1977-07-23','None',2,NULL,'n